Package gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.converter

Class DatatypeConverter

java.lang.Object
gov.cdc.izgw.v2tofhir.converter.DatatypeConverter
public class DatatypeConverter extends Object
DatatypeConverter is the entry point for V2 to FHIR datatype conversion. Operations in DatatypeConverter
  • convert - Generic methods
  • getConverter/converter - Generic Functional Interfaces
  • to{FhirType}(V2 datatype) - Converts to a specified FHIR datatype
  • castInto() - Converts between FHIR Numeric types
Supported FHIR Types:
  • Address
  • Attachment
  • CodeableConcept
  • CodeType
  • Coding
  • ContactPoint
  • DateTimeType
  • DateType
  • DecimalType
  • HumanName
  • Identifier
  • IdType
  • InstantType
  • IntegerType
  • PositiveIntType
  • Quantity
  • Range
  • StringType
  • TimeType
  • UnsignedIntType
  • UriType

    • adjustIfVaries

      public static ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.Type adjustIfVaries(ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.Type type, String name)
      Convert a V2 Varies datatype to its actual datatype Used internally in DatatypeConverter to process data NOTE: This operation works on Varies objects where the datatype is specified elsewhere in the message (such as for OBX-5 where the type is specified in OBX-2). Don't expect this to work well where the HAPI V2 Parser doesn't already know the type.
      Parameters:
      type - The V2 varies object to adjust
      name - The name of the type to convert for generics.
      Returns:
      A V2 Primitive or Composite datatype

    • toInstantType

      public static org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.InstantType toInstantType(String original)
      Convert a string to an instant. This method converts a String to an InstantType. It uses both the HAPI V2 and the FHIR Parsers to attempt to convert the input. First it tries the HAPI V2 parser using the date without any ISO Punctuation. If that fails it uses the FHIR Parser. The two parsers operate differently and have overlapping coverage on their input string ranges, so this provides the highest level of compatibility.
      Parameters:
      original - The value to convert
      Returns:
      An InstantType set to the precision of the timestamp. NOTE: This is a small abuse of InstantType.
